"title": "5745: women",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5745: women",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God created both women and men in his image and likeness. Scripture shows women in a variety of roles, playing an important part in God's salvation plan. In Christ, there is no fundamental distinction between believers on account of gender, race or social status. Women played a significant part in the life of Jesus Christ and in the early church. The NT both records their role and faces the questions thereby raised.</p>\n<h2>The creation of women</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:20–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:1-Gen5:2\">GEN 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:13\">1TI 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>Women and the fall</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:14\">1TI 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:16\">GEN 3:1–3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3\">2CO 11:3</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of godly women</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:16–1:17</a> <em>Ruth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:9-1Sam1:28\">1SA 1:9–1:28</a> <em>Hannah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:2-1Sam25:35\">1SA 25:2–25:35</a> <em>Abigail</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:15-Esth4:16\">EST 4:15–4:16</a> <em>Esther</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:41-Luke1:45\">LUK 1:41–1:45</a> <em>Elizabeth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:36-Acts9:42\">ACT 9:36–9:42</a> <em>Tabitha</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of women who are condemned or judged</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:16-2Sam6:23\">2SA 6:16–6:23</a> <em>Michal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:1-1Kgs21:25\">1KI 21:1–21:25</a> <em>Jezebel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:1-Prov5:6\">PRO 5:1–5:6</a> <em>the adulteress</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:16-Isa4:1\">ISA 3:16–4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:17-Ezek13:23\">EZK 13:17–13:23</a></p>\n<h2>OT laws concerning women</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:22-Exod21:25\">EXO 21:22–21:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:1–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:19-Lev15:30\">LEV 15:19–15:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:5\">DEU 22:5</a></p>\n<h2>Women in office in the OT</h2>\n<h3>As a judge or leader</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4-Judg4:5\">JDG 4:4–4:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>As a prophetess</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:20-Exod15:21\">EXO 15:20–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4\">JDG 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:14-2Kgs22:20\">2KI 22:14–22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:3\">ISA 8:3</a></p>\n<h3>As a queen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:1-2Kgs11:3\">2KI 11:1–11:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:1-1Kgs10:13\">1KI 10:1–10:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:1-2Chr9:12\">2CH 9:1–9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:9-Esth1:21\">EST 1:9–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:17\">EST 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Women as wives and mothers in the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:4\">PRO 12:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:11-Gen21:12\">GEN 21:11–21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:22\">PRO 18:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:31\">PRO 31:10–31:31</a></p>\n<h2>Women in the life of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>In the birth narratives</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:26-Luke1:56\">LUK 1:26–1:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:16-Luke2:19\">LUK 2:16–2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:36-Luke2:38\">LUK 2:36–2:38</a></p>\n<h3>In the ministry of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:1-Luke8:3\">LUK 8:1–8:3</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ respected women and talked to them as individuals with spiritual understanding. This was a considerable deviation from the cultural conventions of the time.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20-Matt9:22\">MAT 9:20–9:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:34\">MRK 5:25–5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:43-Luke8:48\">LUK 8:43–8:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:41-Mark12:44\">MRK 12:41–12:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:1-Luke21:4\">LUK 21:1–21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:38-Luke10:42\">LUK 10:38–10:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:7-John4:30\">JHN 4:7–4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:17-John11:44\">JHN 11:17–11:44</a></p>\n<h3>In the passion narratives</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:55-Matt27:56\">MAT 27:55–27:56</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:40-Mark15:41\">MRK 15:40–15:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:49\">LUK 23:49</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:13\">MAT 26:6–26:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3-Mark14:9\">MRK 14:3–14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37-Luke7:38\">LUK 7:37–7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:1-John12:8\">JHN 12:1–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:61\">MAT 27:61</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:47\">MRK 15:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:55-Luke23:56\">LUK 23:55–23:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:1-Matt28:10\">MAT 28:1–28:10</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1-Mark16:11\">MRK 16:1–16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1-Luke24:11\">LUK 24:1–24:11</a></p>\n<h2>Women's ministry in the early church</h2>\n<h3>As prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:8-Acts21:9\">ACT 21:8–21:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17-Acts2:18\">ACT 2:17–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28-Joel2:29\">JOL 2:28–2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:5\">1CO 11:5</a></p>\n<h3>As teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:3-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:3–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:24-Acts18:26\">ACT 18:24–18:26</a></p>\n<h3>As deacons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:1-Rom16:2\">ROM 16:1–16:2</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote at verse 1.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:11\">1TI 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>As hostesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:15\">COL 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:19\">1CO 16:19</a></p>\n<h3>As workers in the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:12\">ROM 16:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:6\">ROM 16:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:2-Phil4:3\">PHP 4:2–4:3</a></p>\n<h3>As an apostle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:7\">ROM 16:7</a></strong> <em>Interpreters disagree over whether Junias was a man or a woman, and also over whether Paul meant these two were notable in the ranks of the apostles or were well-known to the apostles.</em></p>\n<h2>Instructions to women in the early church community</h2>\n<h3>Their role in the church meetings</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:5-1Cor11:16\">1CO 11:5–11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:33-1Cor14:35\">1CO 14:33–14:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:11-1Tim2:12\">1TI 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Their behaviour as Christians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:9-1Tim2:10\">1TI 2:9–2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:11-1Tim5:16\">1TI 5:11–5:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:3-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:3–2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:1–3:6</a></p>\n<h2>The care of women in the early church community</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1\">ACT 6:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1-1Tim5:10\">1TI 5:1–5:10</a></p>\n<h2>Women as the weaker sex</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:13-1Tim2:14\">1TI 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Women and their relationships</h2>\n<h3>Their relationship to God through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26-Gal3:29\">GAL 3:26–3:29</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Their relationship to their husbands</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:2-Rom7:3\">ROM 7:2–7:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:1-1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:1–7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10-1Cor7:16\">1CO 7:10–7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:39-1Cor7:40\">1CO 7:39–7:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:24\">EPH 5:22–5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:33\">EPH 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18\">COL 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:4-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:1–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>Their relationship to men</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a></strong> <em>Some interpret this as referring to a husband, rather than to men generally.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:7-1Cor11:12\">1CO 11:7–11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:11-1Tim2:12\">1TI 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h2>Feminism and the Bible's teaching on women</h2>\n<h3>The equality of the sexes and rejection of female subordination</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:11-1Cor11:12\">1CO 11:11–11:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:28\">GAL 3:28</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of the abuse of women by men</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:30-Judg11:40\">JDG 11:30–11:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:22-Judg19:30\">JDG 19:22–19:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:20\">2SA 13:1–13:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16-Acts16:21\">ACT 16:16–16:21</a></p>\n<h3>Women who are strong role models</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4\">JDG 4:4</a> <em>Deborah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:14-2Kgs22:20\">2KI 22:14–22:20</a> <em>Huldah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:31\">PRO 31:10–31:31</a> <em>the wife of noble character</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:1-Song3:5\">SNG 3:1–3:5</a> <em>the beloved</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:13-Acts16:15\">ACT 16:13–16:15</a> <em>Lydia</em></p>",
